HEADWORD: Well-spoken
<hw>Well"-spo`ken</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Well</ets>
+ <ets>speak</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Speaking well; speaking with fitness or grace;
speaking kindly.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A knight <xex>well-spoken</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Spoken with propriety; <as>as, <ex>well-spoken</ex>
words</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wellspring</ent>⟦br⟧
